cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY

The paper discusses spiking neural networks (SNNs) and their effectiveness in image classification, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The use of spike timing-dependent plasticity (STDP) for unsupervised learning suggests a focus on neural networks (cs.NE) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also proposes a new pre-processing step for image classification, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the potential implementation of the proposed method on neuromorphic hardware suggests a focus on systems and control (cs.SY).
